# NamingConvention

## Section Numbering Schema

Documents use a three-part OR two-part numeric prefix: `XX.Y - {Optional Group Subject:} Title.md`

- `XX` - major topic group (zero-padded, e.g. `01`, `10`)
- `.Y` - minor position within a group (`.0` for primary; `.1`, `.2`, ... for inserted docs)
- Example sequence: `05.0`, `05.1`, `05.2`

Groub Subject is optional, use to group related documents together.

Example:
XX.Y - Figma Linter: Limitations.md
XX.Y - Figma Linter: Token Studio Specification.md
XX.Y - GPFP: GutenPress Figma Plugin Summary.md
XX.Y - GPFP: Architecture Schema.md
XX.Y - Styling Architecture.md


## Renaming to preserve logical order

- If a new doc must precede an existing minor-version doc, rename the existing one to make room.
- Example: inserting a new `05.1` pushes the old `05.1` to `05.2`.
- Use `@.cursor/_tools/rename_reorder.py` for all numbering rename/reorder operations.
- Prefer deterministic CLI execution (`scan`, then `apply-spec`) over ad-hoc/manual renames.

## Referencing design docs

- When referencing design doc files, use the naming convention placeholder format (`XX.Y`) rather than hard-coded numbers.
- Example reference style: `XX.Y - {Group Subject if used:} Title.md`
- Reason: numeric prefixes are renumbered dynamically, and hard-coded numeric references can break after reorder operations.
